headline: Cisco Was the Dot-Com Bust’s Biggest Loser. Now It’s at a 25-Year High.
summary: Cisco was trading around $66.21, putting it on track for its highest close since Sept. 7, 2000. Strong earnings and AI are giving it a boost.

headline: 3 Dividend Stocks to Double Up on Right Now
summary: Dividend-paying networking giant Cisco is in the midst of a comeback.  It's likely too early to give up on Target, a Dividend King in the retailing space.  Fortunately, a poor stock performance can allow investors to buy at a lower valuation while simultaneously earning a higher return on the dividend, often one exceeding the S&P 500 average dividend yield of 1.3%.
